# pyright Guidance

## Project Context

- pyright version: {{ pyright_version | default("detected by Akira") }}
- Config file: {{ config_file | default("pyrightconfig.json or pyproject.toml") }}
- Python version: {{ python_version | default("detected by Akira") }}

## Configuration

- Keep configuration in `pyrightconfig.json` or `[tool.pyright]` in
  `pyproject.toml`; avoid duplicate settings in both.
- Set `typeCheckingMode` deliberately: `off`, `basic`, `standard`, or
  `strict`.
- Keep `include`, `exclude`, and virtual environment settings aligned with the
  project source layout.
- Remember that VSCode Pylance uses pyright, so config changes affect editor
  diagnostics as well as CI.

## Type Errors

- Fix the source of the mismatch before relaxing `typeCheckingMode`.
- Use `reportMissingImports` and stub packages to handle third-party libraries
  without types.
- Use `useLibraryCodeForTypes` when a package has no stubs but useful inline
  annotations or inspectable source.
- Keep casts and protocol boundaries close to the dynamic API they describe.

