## Python 3.10+

- Prefer `X | None` over `Optional[X]`.
- Use built-in collection generics such as `list[str]`.
{% endif %}

## Suppressions

- Pyright-specific suppressions use
  `# pyright: ignore[reportMissingImports]` or the precise report code.
- Do not rely on mypy-style `# type: ignore` for pyright-only suppressions.
- Keep suppressions narrow and local; document dynamic behavior when it is not
  obvious from the code.

## Avoid

- Disabling `reportMissingImports` globally when a stub package or targeted
  ignore would solve the issue.
- Lowering `typeCheckingMode` to hide errors in newly edited code.
- Blanket pyright ignores without a report code.
- Assuming Pylance diagnostics are separate from pyright configuration.
